I"<p>At the close of my 10-week User Acquisition Marketing course at General Assembly, I was tasked with designing a feasible user acquisition plan with logical hypotheses. I chose to use <a href="http://www.asana.com">Asana</a> as the subject of my mock plan. <a href="#fn1">[1]</a></p>

<p>The plan includes:</p>
<ul>
  <li>A complete media plan infused with back-o-the-envelope calculations estimating CLV (customer lifetime value) and CAC (customer acquisition cost)</li>
  <li>A few channels: paid search, display, social, content, and earned media</li>
  <li>Rube Goldberg- and Occam’s Razor-influenced creative</li>
  <li>An image from one of my favorite books on the closing slide</li>
</ul>

<p>Check it out below or over at <a href="http://www.slideshare.net/vincentbarr/mock-user-acquisition-marketing-plan&quot;">Slideshare</a>. Feel free to leave feedback and, if you want a copy, just <a href="mailto:vincentvbarr@gmail.com">email me</a> and it’s yours.</p>

